text: Heathen Chemistry is the fifth studio album by English rock band Oasis, released in 2002. It was the final album with drummer Alan White who left in 2004. White was replaced with Zak Starkey. ==Track listing== ==Band members== ===Oasis=== * Liam Gallagher – lead vocals, tambourine * Noel Gallagher – guitars, vocals * Gem Archer – guitars * Andy Bell – bass * Alan White – drums Category:Oasis (band) albums Category:2002 albums Category:Epic Records albums Category:Rock albums
title: Heathen Chemistry
